---
source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: "help(&[\"inspect\"])"
---
Query various internal filesystem information.

Access advanced information about filesystem internals including inode
resolution, logical extent to physical block mapping, subvolume IDs, chunk
layout, and other diagnostic data. These commands are primarily useful for
debugging, analysis, and recovery operations. Most operations require
CAP_SYS_ADMIN.

Usage: inspect <COMMAND>

Commands:
  rootid            Get tree ID of the containing subvolume of path
  inode-resolve     Get file system paths for the given inode
  logical-resolve   Get file system paths for the given logical address
  subvolid-resolve  Get subvolume ID and tree ID of the given path
  map-swapfile      Print physical extents of a file suitable for swap
  min-dev-size      Print the minimum size a device can be shrunk to
  dump-tree         Dump tree blocks from a btrfs filesystem
  dump-super        Dump the btrfs superblock from a device or image file
  tree-stats        Print statistics about trees in a btrfs filesystem
  list-chunks       List all chunks in the filesystem, one row per stripe
  help              Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
